<plot>It's 5 a.m. and a dozen solitudes animate the streets of the sleeping city. Their private universe is soon disrupted by the daily hustle of an anonymous crowd. Somewhere under these roofs, a small girl asks her grandfather: "What does it mean to be an adult?," a question which contains all the paradox of the people who have the world in their hands.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?181329</url></doc>
